Description: Life expectancy at birth: the expected lifespan of a newborn based on prevailing mortality patterns at the time of birth.
GNI per capita is the gross national income, converted to U.S. dollars using the World Bank Atlas method, divided by the midyear population.
Under-five mortality rate is the probability per 1,000 that a newborn baby will die before reaching age five, if subject to age-specific mortality rates of the specified year.
Level of current health expenditure expressed as a percentage of GDP.
